    excerpt: "Product pages are where SEO traffic becomes revenue \u2014 yet most Shopify stores ship them with duplicate supplier copy and broken schema. Here's the full fix.",
    content: "Product pages convert search traffic into revenue \u2014 but they're the most neglected SEO surface on most Shopify stores. Here is the complete optimization stack.\n\n## Title structure that matches real searches\n\nProduct buyers search in patterns: brand + product + variant (\"Versace Eros EDT 3.4 oz\"). Your product titles and title tags should mirror this exactly. Front-load the brand, include the size/variant in the title, and never waste title characters on slogans.\n\n## The duplicate supplier-description problem\n\nStores importing catalogs (dropshipping especially) publish the same manufacturer descriptions as hundreds of competitors. Google won't rank the 400th copy. The fix: rewrite descriptions in prose with genuinely useful specifics \u2014 materials, scent notes, fit guidance, use cases. For large catalogs, prioritize rewriting your top-margin and top-traffic products first, then work down; even AI-assisted rewriting beats verbatim duplication if you edit for accuracy and brand tone.\n\n## Product schema done fully\n\nMinimum viable: Product schema with name, image, description, brand, sku, gtin, offers (price, currency, availability). Add AggregateRating once reviews exist. This unlocks price/availability/review rich results \u2014 the difference between a plain blue link and a listing with stars and stock status.\n\n## Duplicate-content traps unique to Shopify\n\n- Products in multiple collections generate /collections/x/products/y URL variants \u2014 ensure canonicals point to /products/y (most themes do; verify)\n- Size variants as separate products split authority \u2014 consolidate to one product with variants\n- Tag and vendor pages create thin near-duplicates \u2014 noindex low-value ones\n\n## Internal linking product pages actually need\n\nLink from blog content and buying guides into products with descriptive anchors; cross-link related products in prose (not just app widgets); link every product to its parent collection. Isolated product pages rank poorly regardless of on-page quality.\n\n---\n\n**Need help implementing this?** eCeez builds and optimizes Shopify stores for DTC brands. [Explore our Shopify SEO services](/seo) or [get a store built in days](/shopify-store-setup-service).",
