    content: "Email flows are the closest thing ecommerce has to passive income: built once, they convert around the clock. Here are the seven that matter, ranked by revenue impact \u2014 and the settings that separate performing flows from spam.\n\n## 1. Abandoned cart (highest ROI, always)\n\nThree emails: 1 hour (helpful reminder, no discount), 24 hours (social proof + answers to objections), 72 hours (incentive if your margins allow). Broken or missing abandonment flows are the single most expensive gap we find auditing stores \u2014 recovering even 5\u201310% of abandoned carts often equals a store's entire ad-driven profit.\n\n## 2. Browse abandonment\n\nVisitors who viewed products but never carted. Softer touch: \"still thinking about X?\" with the product, reviews, and related items. Lower volume than cart abandonment, surprisingly comparable conversion.\n\n## 3. Welcome series\n\nYour list's first impression: deliver the signup incentive instantly, tell the brand story in email 2, best-sellers with social proof in email 3. Subscribers convert at their highest rate in the first 72 hours \u2014 don't waste them on a single coupon blast.\n\n## 4. Post-purchase\n\nOrder confirmation upsell (add-to-order window), shipping updates, then usage/care content that prevents returns and primes reviews. This flow builds the second purchase before the first arrives.\n\n## 5. Win-back\n\nCustomers silent for 60\u2013120 days (calibrate to your repurchase cycle \u2014 fragrance ~90 days, consumables shorter). Escalate: new arrivals \u2192 social proof \u2192 incentive.\n\n## 6. Back-in-stock\n\nHighest-intent email you can send; automate it on inventory sync and it converts absurdly well with zero creative effort.\n\n## 7. Review request\n\nTimed post-delivery (not post-order). Reviews compound everything else \u2014 product page conversion, SEO rich results, ad creative.\n\n## The settings that matter\n\nSend from a real reply-able address, suppress purchasers from abandonment flows instantly, and cap discounting \u2014 flows that train customers to abandon carts for coupons eat their own margin.\n\n---\n\n**Want higher conversions?** Our team runs data-backed CRO programs for Shopify brands. [See our CRO services](/cro) or [contact us](/contact) for a free store audit.",
